🔥SPINACH DIP IN A BREAD BOWL 🥬 

One of our most popular dishes to make for any event/party and it’s always a fan favorite 😍

1 round loaf of bread 
16oz sour cream 
8oz  cream cheese 
8 tbsp salted butter 
1 tbsp garlic 
12 oz mozzarella cheese 
1/2 cup Parmesan cheese 
1 block or bag of frozen spinach 
1 can of artichoke (chopped)
Salt and pepper to taste 

Cut a 1 inch slice from the top of the loaf of bread. Hollow out the loaf by cutting along the edge with a serrated knife, leaving a 1 1/2 inch shell then pulling out large chunks of bread (use this for dipping later). In a large pan, add the garlic and butter over medium heat. Once melted, add the cream cheese and allow to melt almost fully then mix in the sour cream. Add the frozen spinach and once it’s fully melted down into the mixture, add the chopped artichokes. Add the cheese and mix until fully combined. Remove from the heat and pour into the bread bowl. Sprinkle with Parmesan and enjoy! 
.

🍫The easiest OREO dessert dip 🔥

1 cup powdered sugar 
8oz of cool whip 
10oz softened cream cheese 
18 - 20 Oreos 

Start by separating the Oreo creme filling from the cookie and place in separate bowls. Crush your Oreos into small pieces (you don’t want them completely crushed-you want small pieces) then set aside. In a large mixing bowl combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and the Oreo creme filling using a hand mixer until smooth. Add the crushed Oreos (leaving just a small amount to garnish) and fold in the cool whip. Place in a serving bowl and garnish with any remaining Oreo crumbs. Serve and ENJOY with your favorite dippers! 🍓
.
.
.

🍫 HOSTESS/LITTLE DEBBIE CUPCAKES 🎂

Our next childhood throwback recipe is the famous Hostess/Little Debbie creme filled chocolate cupcakes. Who remembers and how did we do? 🔥

Cupcakes:
1 cup all purpose flour
1/2 cup cake flour
1/2 cup cocoa powder
3/4 cup sugar 
1 egg
1/2 cup vegetable oil
1/2 cup milk
1/2 cup hot water 
1/2 tsp salt 
1 tsp vanilla
1 tsp baking soda 

Marshmallow filling:
1/2 cup heavy cream 
1/2 cup marshmallow creme or fluff 

Ganache: 
1/4 cup heavy cream 
1/4-1/2 cup chocolate chips 

Icing:
1/2 cup powdered sugar
1 tbsp heavy cream 

Preheat your oven to 310F. In a large mixing bowl, combine the milk, vegetable oil, egg, sugar, vanilla, and hot water. Sift in the two types of flours, salt, baking soda and cocoa powder. Mix until smooth. Fill your cupcake tins about halfway. Bake for 20 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Allow to cool down. Make the filling by whipping the heavy cream until stiff peaks form then add the marshmallow creme in and whisk until combined. Pour into a piping bag or ziplock bag. Core the center of your cupcakes leaving a small space of cupcake at the bottom. Fill the hole with the marshmallow filling and top with the removed cupcake piece. Make your ganache by microwaving for about 30 seconds the heavy cream and chocolate chips. Dip the cupcakes into the ganache and allow to dry or (pop in the freezer for 10 min). Make your icing by combining the two ingredients and design the top of your cupcakes in “loops”. ....ENJOY! 😍
.
.
.

🌈 FUNFETTI BLONDIES 🔥 

Working on so many new recipes to share very soon, here’s a sneak peek! 

1/2 cup chopped white chocolate 
1/3 cup sprinkles 
1 cup flour 
1/2 cup butter 
1/2 cup brown sugar 
1/4 cup white sugar 
1/2 tsp salt 
1/2 tsp baking powder 
1 tsp vanilla 
2 eggs 

Preheat oven to 350F. Microwave butter until partially melted in a large bowl. Add the sugars and vanilla then mix. Add the eggs and mix again. Fold in the flour, baking powder and salt until combined. Add the chopped white chocolate and sprinkles. Mix until incorporated and pour the mixture into a 8x8 pan lined with parchment paper. Bake for 28-30 minutes and allow to cool completely before removing from the pan ✨
.
.

🍫OREO CHEESECAKE SLU*TY BROWNIES 🔥

Brownie layer:
1/3 cup heavy cream
1 cup chocolate chips 
4 tbsp butter
2 eggs
1/3 cup sugar
1/4 cup cocoa powder 
1/2 cup flour

Cheesecake layer: 
1/3 cup heavy cream 
6oz cream cheese 
1/3 cup sugar 
1 tsp vanilla 
1 egg 
Crushed Oreos 

Cookie layer:
1/2 cup salted butter 
1/2 cup brown sugar 
1/4 cup white sugar 
1 tsp vanilla
1 egg 
1 cup cake flour 
1/2 tsp baking soda 
1 cup chocolate chips 

Combine all ingredients for each layer separately. In pan lined with parchment paper, add the brownie mixture. Top with a layer of Oreos. Add the cheesecake layer and then the cookie layer. Bake on 350F for 45-50 minutes or until done in the center! 
.
.
.
.
